body:
the story is I am working on writing a contract of a token with hardhat on VS code and  I created and wrote all the contents needed including ownable, safe math, context, IERC20, ERC20 and Token.

here is the contract for the token and I drop it here as it is short:

// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity ^0.8.19;

import "./ERC20.sol";

contract Token is ERC20
{
  
    constructor () ERC20("Token", "SMD", 1000000 * 1e5, 5){
      _balances[_msgSender()] = 1000000 * 1e5;

    }
}

--------------------------------------------------------------
and here is the constructor part in the ERC20 contract:

constructor(string memory name_, string memory  symbol_, uint totalSupply_, uint decimals_)
  {
    _name = name_;
    _symbol = symbol_;
    _totalSupply = totalSupply_;
    _decimals = decimals_;

  }

--------------------------------------------------------------
the problem is that everything seems accurate as I double checked with different courses and asked ChatGPT but it keeps giving me this error either on Token and ERC20 contract:
No arguments passed to the base constructor. Specify the arguments or mark "Token" as abstract.solidity(3415)
No arguments passed to the base constructor. Specify the arguments or mark "ERC20" as abstract.solidity(3415)

marking the contract as abstract removes the error but it doesn't let me to deploy it.

is there anyone that can help me with this I would appreciate it?
